<li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cynthia A. Freeland, <i>But Is It Art?: An Introduction to Art Theory</i>, Oxford University Press (2001), page 95</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFRudy2007" class="citation book cs1">Rudy, Kathryn M. (2007). <i>Weaving, Veiling and Dressing: Textiles and their Metaphors in the Late Middle Ages</i>. Brepols. p.&#160;3.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Weaving%2C+Veiling+and+Dressing%3A+Textiles+and+their+Metaphors+in+the+Late+Middle+Ages&amp;rft.pages=3&amp;rft.pub=Brepols&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.aulast=Rudy&amp;rft.aufirst=Kathryn+M.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChristian+art" class="Z3988"></span></span>
